title: For Sale:  Daniel Defense M4 14.5" clone upper
postcontent:
For sale is an M4 clone upper I built around the following parts:

-Daniel Defense 14.5" CHF 1:7 carbine barrel
-BCM blemish upper receiver
-Colt carry handle rear sight
-VLTOR Gunfighter Mod.3 CH
-KAC M4 RAS
-Colt sling swivel
-FN flash hider

The legit "been there done that parts" are the Colt carry handle, KAC M4 RAS, FN A2 flash hider, and Colt sling swivel.

The BCM upper, and VLTOR Gunfighter CH were new parts that I "fauxed" by hand.

The Daniel Defense barrel was new, and I didn't have the heart to "faux" it, so it's unmolested :)

The A2 FH was a practice piece for pin welding with a shitty arc welder. The barrel, however, was NOT drilled, or welded on, etc. Virgin barrel, and NOT pinned. All NFA rules apply. (I have an extended A2 flash hider available for another $25)

Barrel nut *properly* torqued to 42 pounds using Aeroshell 33MS. Feedramps line up perfect. FSB is nice and straight. KAC M4 RAS is LOCK-SOLID with no wobble whatsoever.

The upper was test fired with 90 rounds of M855, and functioned flawlessly with an H2 buffer. Damn accurate barrel. I chose the DD CHF over the standard Colt to be able to handle a bit more piss & vinegar type shooting. This upper you can confidently throw across your driveway and not feel bad about it. Includes three KAC rail panels as pictured. This would make an ideal upper for a truck gun, "loaner" gun, clone piece, paint/cerakote project. Or part the thing out and make some money...

title: For Sale:  100 rounds - 7.62x39mm - Wolf Performance, Bi-metal Jacket
postcontent:
Hello,


     My name is Thomas Emard. Some of you Armslisters may have dealt with me regarding Mosin-Nagants or SKS rifles. I have started up my own ammunition company, Vexxer Munitions, and I decided to give my local Armslisters first grab at the ammunition. My selection is limited at the moment; I thought it better to keep a few types of ammunition in stock, rather than buy a bit of lots of types.

    This ammunition is very solid. I won't say it's amazing, because let's face it, Wolf will never be a 'performance' round. But that being said, I've fired well over 10,000 rounds through my various AK's and SKS', and not a single one misfired or jammed.

    Up for sale is 100 rounds, for $28. I have 10 in stock at the moment. A discount will be offered for bulk purchases. If you need some cheap ammunition for a shooting trip, or you're a prepper and you want to start stocking up on the world's most common bullet, this ad is for you!


    Contact me anytime with questions, and do make sure to check out my other ads. At the moment, all I'm offering for ammunition is 7.62x39mm and 7.62x54R, but I do have quite a few rifles and shotguns lying around for sale or trade.

    I'd also like to take a moment and thank you personally, Armlister. You, and hundreds like you, have kept Portland's gun community strong. My first ad on here, I asked for Mosins. I was expecting a dozen, perhaps. I was stunned with the results; over the course of 4 weeks, two HUNDRED Mosins were offered for sale. So, thank you for using Armslist instead of your local gun dealer. The stronger the community becomes, the farther prices drop and the more selection we get. It is this fact that convinced me to post this ammunition for sale here, weeks in advance of my proper store being opened to the general American public.

As my business grows and I am able to place larger orders, the price will drop. Significantly. As it stands, I am making mere pennies on each order of 100 rounds, but I'd rather make tiny profit than have these rounds sitting around waiting for someone desperate enough to pay 'scalper' prices.


Regards,
     Thomas

title: For Sale:  Marlin 1894 in .44 Magnum
postcontent:
I bought this in 1991 but it sat forlorn in various closets till last week, when I finally took it to the range to finally fire it. 20 rounds suggests this .44 magnum is just too much gun for me. And my bills came (ouch) and my niece is getting married (and she's anti-gun so I can't just give it to her), so I might as well get what cash I can from it.

The only things wrong with this gun are cosmetic: there's a slight scratch in the finish of the stock (which might not show up too well), the folding leaf rear sight is broken off, and now there are a couple ugly but not fatal scratches on/near the sight from where I tried and failed to install a replacement as shown in that photo. I figured out how to avoid scratching it again but not how to get the flimsy little plastic thing on without breaking it; then again the forums lead me to think a lot of folks buy yourselves niftier sights or install a scope anyway so instead of going through that again I'm just asking less than I'd planned. The rear folding leaf is $7.99 plus $7.95 S&H from Brownell's if you'd rather do that and can get it on without breaking it, I do still have the little sight extender thing.

By the way, this booming slugger does have a cross-bar safety. It also has a Micro-Grooved barrel so factory ammo works fine, but I read on the web someplace that home-cast bullets have to be a tiny bit bigger around to aim well.

I'll listen to suggestions about a partial trade, but as previously noted there's got to be enough cash involved. Sorry about that.
